@wyattscarpenter It looks like the logic for [walking up the dg_stack](https://github.com/streamlit/streamlit/blob/develop/lib/streamlit/elements/form.py#L56) is causing this, since by the time you run the final `with e` statement the `dg_stack` no longer contains a form.

I am thinking the more correct behavior here would be to simply get `this_dg._active_dg` and then start walking up the `parent` chain until you hit a form. That should handle both of the current cases (calling as `dg.foo` or as `st.foo`) and should also handle your case as well, I think.

Aside: I am also noticing that the current code only walks ONE level up, which means if you have a form with nested empties/containers/etc I think you might run into other issues where it doesn't think you're a descendent of a form dg when you actually are.
